{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"58ad6c6e-5602-4204-bb2b-687a07f110f4","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n**1. Project file — `MyTests.csproj`**\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net9.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\n`MSTest.Sdk` replaces the typical `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` and auto-includes `MSTest`, the runner, and code-coverage — no `<PackageReference>` items needed.\n\n**2. Enable parallelism — add a `.runsettings` or assembly attribute**\n\nThe simplest way is a single file `Usings.cs`:\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]\n```\n\nThis runs all test **methods** in parallel (use `ClassLevel` to parallelize classes but run methods within a class sequentially).\n\n**3. Force database tests to run sequentially**\n\nDecorate your database test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Read_Record()   { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\nAll methods in that class will run sequentially **after** the parallel batch finishes.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of the three moving parts:**\n\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---|---|\n| Minimal project file | `MSTest.Sdk/3.8` as the SDK |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` |\n| Sequential DB tests | `[DoNotParallelize]` on the class |\n\nNo extra NuGet packages, no `.runsettings` file required. Want me to scaffold these files in the working directory?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d59cc800-15ae-4ea6-a3ef-1f0764491d87","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory is empty and there are no plugins. Let me provide the recommended MSTest setup based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":496,"requestId":"5817:1007E7:5A28E0F:6224B0F:6A03394A"},"id":"afebd89b-20b3-4d75-98da-9708f98b7c3e","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:29:42.939Z","parentId":"ecc6ed91-9b2b-4992-9241-b08d3af8798c"}
